HEADWORD: Discriminant
<hw>Dis*crim"i*nant</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>discriminans</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>discriminare</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Math.)</fld> <def>The eliminant of the <xex>n</xex> partial
differentials of any homogeneous function of <xex>n</xex> variables. See
<er>Eliminant</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

